snippet.textDisplay:
Shantanu Moitra,
Vanakampa. Nanu Tunga Poravu. Now, I know you appa. I will watch your songs what I ever I get.
Ushagaru, Nenu "same previous comment ni post chesthunnanu". "Maaf karo Muje". Now, I got pure masala. Rest of the shows I will finish them little later.
------------------------
Usha(ji/garu),
I love your voice. And LR Eswari's voice. My wife asks why you love them so much. I used say - they sing from heart/feeling/emotion as is and it does not require any training (I love RD Burman and Ilaya Raja). It comes naturally. My son's name is Sangeeth (music) and my daughter's Sahaja (nature) - after my father's name  Sleevaiah (Jesus) who is an Gov officer and used to have Hormoniam (Key board). I used his key board when was 10 yrs old and got playing on it within 3 days and then I started playing any instrument I see. These things came from me going to Church every day morning and evening and then going to Hanuman Temple. When I was in teen age, I used to list out 10 audio tapes of Telugu and Hindi songs - especially for Lorry workers and every one for customers of one of my friend's audio recording center. I was doing every thing naturally including practicing Homeo medicine. Because of my fathers suggestions I did studies and went to San Fracisco Bay Area in 1992 as a Software Engineer. In our SF Bay Area Indian Radio station, I listen to and talk to every day. It started 7 years ago and I am listener since then.

Namsthe/Van(akkam/dhanam),
Babu Alluri.
